50|$|Tryon {{is called}} back to Patesville on {{business}} and <b>wants</b> <b>to</b> see Rena again. He is {{still in love with}} her and <b>wants</b> <b>to</b> <b>believe</b> <b>that</b> her family history is a lie. Although Rena refuses to dance at the party, her mother convinces her to dance with Wain. Tryon arrives at the house {{just in time to see}} the couple dancing. He is hurt to find that Rena appears to be happy rather than being depressed and pining for him.|$|R
